DataElement.preferredName: Unified Modeling Language Class Object Class Relationship Administered Item Metadata Bidirectional Relationship Indicator java.lang.Boolean
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A grouping of things based on shared common attributes.:A description of the affiliation between two occurrences of Object Classes.:A registry item for which administrative information is recorded in an Administration Record.:Data about data; information that describes another set of data._Reactive or functioning or allowing movement in two usually opposite directions.:A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something.:An event, entity or condition that typically characterizes a prescribed environment or situation and determines or aids in determining whether certain stated circumstances exist or criteria are satisfied._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Boolean value (true or false).
